Subject: [PATCH 0163/2588] drm/ttm: Initialize eviction placement in case the
 driver callback doesn't

This would allow to catch driver callback error of not properly
setting the eviction placement structure.

Signed-off-by: Jerome Glisse <jglisse@redhat.com>
Signed-off-by: Dave Airlie <airlied@linux.ie>
(cherry picked from commit 7cb7d1d7b650c9764c8a1b00e2b43d932acde779)

Signed-off-by: Takashi Iwai <tiwai@suse.de>
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/ttm/ttm_bo.c |    4 ++++
 1 files changed, 4 insertions(+), 0 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/ttm/ttm_bo.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/ttm/ttm_bo.c
index 640fb26..cf88347 100644
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/ttm/ttm_bo.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/ttm/ttm_bo.c
@@ -584,6 +584,10 @@ static int ttm_bo_evict(struct ttm_buffer_object *bo, bool interruptible,
 	evict_mem = bo->mem;
 	evict_mem.mm_node = NULL;
 
+	placement.fpfn = 0;
+	placement.lpfn = 0;
+	placement.num_placement = 0;
+	placement.num_busy_placement = 0;
 	bdev->driver->evict_flags(bo, &placement);
 	ret = ttm_bo_mem_space(bo, &placement, &evict_mem, interruptible,
 				no_wait);
